commentary: Starc to Broom, SIX runs has he taken it? Hazlewood leaps in the air, right on the edge of the boundary at third man, and comes up with a one-hander. So cool. So calm. Umpire Knight reverses his call, raises his finger, and sends back Handscomb

commentary: Boult to Stoinis, 1 leg bye Has Stoinis nicked it behind? Not given by Palliyaguruge. And they cross over. Latham should have run up and attempted to flick the ball onto the stumps. New Zealand challenge the on-field not out decision. Good-length indipper,cramps the batsman for room. He jams his bat down, the ball grazes the flap of the front pad and carries through to the keeper. Snicko picks up a spike - that's when the ball hit the pad. No clear evidence of an inside snick. Umpire Dharmasena checks from various angles. Excellent awareness from Stoinis and Hazlewood. Not so much from Latham

commentary: Southee to Stoinis, OUT Venue: Eden Park. Hero: Kane Williamson. Result: New Zealand win a thriller! You've heard that before? Whoa.... What a game. Breathless stuff. First let us give credit to Williamson for placing himself at short mid-on. Southee nails a yorker on off stump, Stoinis can only dig the ball out fairly straight to Williamson. He collects the ball, falls in front of the stumps, and under-arms it into the stumps to catch Hazlewood short. Hazlewood had lost his head. He was off for a single - there wasn't a single there - he has to spin back. He dishes out a desperate dive, but that's not enough. This is the first time Hazlewood has been dismissed in an ODI. Spare a thought for Marcus Stonis, though. Nearly pulled off an incredible heist from nowhere
